{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"AbsoluteOrientationSensor()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor/AbsoluteOrientationSensor","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><em><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Sensor API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RelativeOrientationSensor\"><code>RelativeOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SensorErrorEvent\"><code>SensorErrorEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor()</code></strong> constructor creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a> object which describes the device's physical orientation in relation to the Earth's reference coordinate system.</p>\n<p>If a feature policy blocks use of a feature it is because your code is inconsistent with the policies set on your server. This is not something that would ever be shown to a user. The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Feature-Policy\"><code>Feature-Policy</code></a> HTTP header article contains implementation instructions.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">new AbsoluteOrientationSensor()\nnew AbsoluteOrientationSensor(options)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Options are as follows:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"frequency\"><code>frequency</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>The desired number of times per second a sample should be taken, meaning the number of times per second that the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a> event will be called. A whole number or decimal may be used, the latter for frequencies less than a second. The actual reading frequency depends on the device hardware and consequently may be less than requested.</p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"referenceframe\"><code>referenceFrame</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>Either <code>'device'</code> or <code>'screen'</code>. The default is <code>'device'</code>.</p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/orientation-sensor/#dom-absoluteorientationsensor-absoluteorientationsensor","title":"Orientation Sensor"}],"query":"api.AbsoluteOrientationSensor.AbsoluteOrientationSensor"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.AbsoluteOrientationSensor.AbsoluteOrientationSensor","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor/AbsoluteOrientationSensor/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a> event</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The AbsoluteOrientationSensor() constructor creates a new AbsoluteOrientationSensor object which describes the device's physical orientation in relation to the Earth's reference coordinate system.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:04:34.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/absoluteorientationsensor/absoluteorientationsensor","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/absoluteorientationsensor/absoluteorientationsensor/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/fae225dc7876dd22800d39dffff0d663ee7808aa","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor","title":"AbsoluteOrientationSensor"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor/AbsoluteOrientationSensor","title":"AbsoluteOrientationSensor()"}],"pageTitle":"AbsoluteOrientationSensor() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}